lyrics:
[Verse]
I saw you standing there, in aisle number nine
Eyes locked in a gaze, I knew you were mine
We danced through the aisles, like a dream come true
In this supermarket love, I found solace in you

[Chorus]
Supermarket love, a serenade of aisles
Our hearts intertwined, can't help but smile
In this ordinary place, our love does ignite
Supermarket love, a sweet rendezvous in plain sight
